## Session Citation Rules

- Every proposal MUST include `session_ids`. An empty list is NOT acceptable when the pattern was observed in any session.
- If a proposal has no supporting sessions, drop the proposal entirely.
- To cite a session, copy the full UUID.
- The `(index=N)` suffix is for step references, NOT session citation. Never put the integer into `session_ids`.
- Long sessions may appear split across multiple headers as `uuid__part1`, `uuid__part2`, ... Cite just the base UUID once (the service deduplicates).
- Cite only sessions where the pattern was actually observed. If you referenced a session in `example_refs`, also include it in `session_ids`.
